g errors, these two fits are substantially and statistically different.\nSuch differences amongst fits using different filters and models are a\ncautionary tale regarding our current ability to fit star cluster\ncolor-magnitude diagrams. Additional modeling of this kind, with more models\nand star clusters, and future GAIA parallaxes are critical for isolating and\nquantifying the most relevant uncertainties in stellar evolutionary models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Jan 2015 21:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
